hey experience symptoms that could indicate the occurrence of torsade de pointes such as dizziness, lightheadedness, fainting, palpitation, irregular heart rhythm, shortness of breath, or syncope.', 'Synergism', 'Tamsulosin, Tinidazole, Ascorbic acid, Hydroflumethiazide, Chlorothiazide, Simeprevir, Sulfadiazine, Lactic acid, Mitapivat, Methazolamide, Amphotericin B, More', 'Lamivudine, Paritaprevir, Tenofovir alafenamide, Simeprevir, Cabotegravir, Valaciclovir, Zanamivir, Oseltamivir, Acyclovir, Brincidofovir, Stavudine, More', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/288595/', '[1] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[2] Canadian Pharmacists Association "e-CPS.  http://www.pharmacists.ca/function/Subscriptions/ecps.cfm?link=eCPS_quikLink"   (2006):[3] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[4] "Product Information. Zelboraf (vemurafenib)." Genentech  (2011):', 1767369485);
