tients experiencing new, worsening, or recurrent hepatotoxicity may require a delay, change in dosage, or discontinuation of brentuximab vedotin in accordance with the product labeling.', 'Synergism', 'Felodipine, Amlodipine, Bisoprolol, Hydrochlorothiazide, Indapamide', 'Pertuzumab, Cetuximab, Avelumab, Panitumumab, Obinutuzumab, Bevacizumab, Necitumumab, Dostarlimab, Ramucirumab, Atezolizumab, Amivantamab, More', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/288616/', '[1] "Product Information. Adcetris (brentuximab vedotin)." Seattle Genetics Inc  (2011):', 1767369485);
